        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Token Usage Is an Operational Signal"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For most web services, resource usage (CPU, memory, bandwidth) is a background concern visible only when something breaks. For Claude integrations, token usage is a first-class operational signal: it determines cost, drives rate limiting, and reveals quality regressions that no latency or error metric can detect."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A prompt that grew by 500 tokens due to a context accumulation bug produces no errors, no latency spike, and no alert \u2014 but it silently doubles your monthly bill and consumes your token quota twice as fast. Tracking token usage as an operational signal catches these regressions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
