        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost anomalies are best detected by comparing the current input/output token ratio against the baseline. A healthy Claude integration has a relatively stable ratio: if you typically send 1000 input tokens and receive 300 output tokens per request, a ratio of 1 : 0.3 is normal. Deviations expose specific bugs:"
          }
