        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Token Budget Alerts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# prometheus/alerts/claude-token-cost.yaml\ngroups:\n  - name: claude_token_cost\n    rules:\n      # Alert when estimated monthly cost exceeds budget by 20%\n      - alert: ClaudeEstimatedCostOverBudget\n        expr: |\n          (\n            sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_input_total{model=\"claude-sonnet-5\"}[1h])) * 3\n            + sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_output_total{model=\"claude-sonnet-5\"}[1h])) * 15\n            + sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_input_total{model=\"claude-opus-4-8\"}[1h])) * 15\n            + sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_output_total{model=\"claude-opus-4-8\"}[1h])) * 75\n            + sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_input_total{model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"}[1h])) * 0.8\n            + sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_output_total{model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"}[1h])) * 4\n          ) / 1_000_000 * 24 * 30\n          > 1200  # monthly budget in USD \u00d7 1.20\n        for: 30m\n        labels:\n          severity: warning\n        annotations:\n          summary: \"Claude monthly cost forecast exceeds budget\"\n\n      # Alert when output/input ratio doubles (prompt regression)\n      - alert: ClaudeOutputRatioAnomaly\n        expr: |\n          (sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_output_total[5m])) / sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_input_total[5m])))\n          >\n          (sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_output_total[1d])) / sum(rate(claude_api_tokens_input_total[1d]))) * 2\n        for: 10m\n        labels:\n          severity: warning\n        annotations:\n          summary: \"Claude output/input token ratio is 2\u00d7 the daily baseline \u2014 possible prompt regression\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Token usage is not just a cost metric \u2014 it is an operational signal that reveals prompt regressions, context accumulation bugs, cache invalidation, and model mix shifts that no other metric exposes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Record input and output tokens as counters immediately after each API response, labelled by model and feature."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add cache read and cache creation counters if using prompt caching; cache read fraction is a leading indicator of cache effectiveness."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Compute call cost using model-specific per-million-token prices; wrap in a recording rule for dashboard and alert use."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Monitor the output/input token ratio as a regression detector: a ratio spike without a traffic change usually indicates a prompt template regression."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Attribute cost by feature using a feature label to support product-level cost allocation decisions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Alert on estimated monthly cost exceeding budget and on output/input ratio anomalies."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
